    <desc>How do I tell websites I do not them to monitor my web activites?</desc>
  </info>

  <title>Set web tracking preference</title>

  <p>Websites generally monitor your activity when you visit them. For example,
  they may want to know which pages you view or what you have searched for. This
  information can be used to improve your web browsing experience, but it can
  also be sold can be used to sell or shared with other companies which may use
  it in a malicious way. You can ask websites that you visit to not monitor your
  activity by enabling <gui>Do Not Track</gui>.</p>

  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>Open <guiseq><gui style="menu">Web</gui>
      <gui style="menuitem">Preferences</gui>
      <gui style="tab">Privacy</gui></guiseq>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Tick the <gui style="checkbox">Tell web sites I do no want to
      be tracked</gui> checkbox.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>

  <note style="important">
    <p>Websites do not have to honor this preference.</p>
  </note>

